text: The Seward County Courthouse is a historic building in Seward, Nebraska, and the county courthouse for Seward County. It was built in 1905-1907 on a farm formerly owned by Lewis Moffitt, the founder of Seward. With It was designed in the Classical Revival style by architect George A. Berlinghof. It has been listed on the National Register of Historic Places since January 10, 1990. ==References== Category:Neoclassical architecture in Nebraska Category:County courthouses in Nebraska Category:Government buildings completed in 1905 Category:National Register of Historic Places in Seward County, Nebraska Category:1905 establishments in Nebraska
